definition: disposition of troops/wave/spate/burst/spell/short period of time/classifier for events or states of short duration

sentences.english: Rwanda was in the throes of genocide.
sentences.chinese: 盧旺達陷於種族滅絕的陣痛。

sentences.english: World had to be in travail, that the meanest flower might blow.
sentences.chinese: 社會必須經歷陣痛以便讓最卑微的花開放。

sentences.english: When will labor start, you’re likely wondering?
sentences.chinese: 你可能想知道什麼時候開始陣痛？

sentences.english: But what should you expect when you’re laboring and delivering?
sentences.chinese: 但是當你經歷陣痛和分娩時，你應該期待什麼呢？

sentences.english: It was born amidst the last throes of expiring cults and civilizations in Western Asia and Egypt.
sentences.chinese: 這是由於出生的最後陣痛期邪教和文明在西亞和埃及。

sentences.english: The pregnancy progressed normally for Karen. In, time the labor pains came.
sentences.chinese: 凱倫在娠妊期間一切正常，不久，分娩的陣痛開始了。

definition: variant of 動蕩|动荡[dong4 dang4]
to make progress only with great difficulty (idiom)
(economics) to reduce/to curtail/to cut back/to tighten/austerity/tightening/crunch
to intensify/to sharpen/to accelerate/to aggravate/to exacerbate/to embitter
to face childbirth/about to give birth/refers esp. to the onset of regular contractions
stuck and not moving forward (idiom); stagnant/in a rut/at a standstill
to break up into components/to disintegrate/to collapse/to crumble
